Note: Redis Security Validation Functions

Process called "validate_redis_key" that takes key as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Validate Redis key name for security
    If key is none or key is equal to "":
        Return false
    
    Note: Check key length (Redis has 512MB limit, but we use smaller practical limit)
    If string_length with value as key is greater than 250:
        Return false
    
    Note: Check for dangerous patterns in key names
    Let dangerous_patterns be List with:
        "*"  Note: Wildcard patterns can be dangerous in certain contexts
        "?"  Note: Single character wildcards
        "["  Note: Character class patterns
        "__"  Note: Double underscores often indicate system keys
        "eval:"  Note: Lua script execution patterns
        "script:"  Note: Script-related keys
    
    For each pattern in dangerous_patterns:
        If pattern in key:
            Return false
    
    Note: Check for control characters and non-printable characters
    Let control_chars be List with "\n" and "\r" and "\t" and "\0"
    For each char in control_chars:
        If char in key:
            Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "validate_redis_value" that takes value as Any returns Boolean:
    Note: Validate Redis value for security and size limits
    If value is none:
        Return true  Note: None/null values are acceptable
    
    Let value_type be type_of with value as value
    
    Note: String value validation
    If value_type is equal to "String":
        Let value_str be value as String
        Let value_len be string_length with value as value_str
        
        Note: Prevent excessively large values (DoS protection)
        If value_len is greater than 10000000:  Note: 10MB limit for strings
            Return false
        
        Note: Check for binary data that might cause issues
        Let control_chars be List with "\0" and "\x01" and "\x02"
        For each char in control_chars:
            If char in value_str:
                Return false
    
    Note: Numeric value validation
    If value_type is equal to "Integer" or value_type is equal to "Float":
        Return true  Note: Numeric values are generally safe
    
    Note: List/Array validation
    If value_type is equal to "List":
        Let value_list be value as List[Any]
        If length of value_list is greater than 100000:  Note: Prevent huge lists
            Return false
        
        Note: Validate each item in the list
        For each item in value_list:
            If not validate_redis_value with value as item:
                Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "validate_redis_command" that takes command as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Validate Redis commands for security
    Let command_upper be command as String  Note: Mock uppercase conversion
    
    Note: List of dangerous Redis commands that should be restricted
    Let dangerous_commands be List with:
        "FLUSHDB"  Note: Deletes all data in current database
        "FLUSHALL"  Note: Deletes all data in all databases
        "CONFIG"  Note: Server configuration changes
        "SHUTDOWN"  Note: Server shutdown
        "DEBUG"  Note: Debug commands
        "EVAL"  Note: Lua script execution (can be dangerous)
        "EVALSHA"  Note: Execute Lua script by SHA
        "SCRIPT"  Note: Script management commands
        "MODULE"  Note: Module loading/management
        "ACL"  Note: Access control list management
        "CLIENT"  Note: Client connection management
        "MONITOR"  Note: Server monitoring (performance impact)
        "SYNC"  Note: Replication commands
        "PSYNC"  Note: Partial resync
    
    For each dangerous_cmd in dangerous_commands:
        If dangerous_cmd in command_upper:
            Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "log_security_event" that takes event_type as String and details as String and severity as String returns None:
    Note: Log Redis security events
    Let timestamp be datetime.now as string
    Let log_message be "[" plus timestamp plus "] REDIS_SECURITY [" plus severity plus "]: " plus event_type plus " - " plus details
    
    If severity is equal to "HIGH":
        Call logging.error with message as log_message
    Otherwise if severity is equal to "MEDIUM":
        Call logging.warning with message as log_message
    Otherwise:
        Call logging.info with message as log_message

